  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building climate resilient livelihoods in vulnerable landscapes in Bangladesh (PPG)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To prepare full project proposal, FAO has received 200000 USD from the GEF. This fund will be spent on project preparation activities outlined as 4 activities:Activity 1. Consultation and engagement of local and institutional stakeholders, and definition of project actions for stakeholder engagement, capacity strengthening and policy support; Activity 2: Definition of project actions in support of identifying promising climate resilient livelihoods and adaptation innovations to deliver global environmental benefits; Activity 3: Definition of actions in support of scaling-up investments in the targeted landscapes to reduce vulnerability and increase resilience; and Activity 4: Information Synthesis, Project Design and Budgeting</narrative>
  </description>
